2xx - Success
  - 200 OK
  - 201 Identity Accepted for Review
  - 202 Identity Confirmed
  - 203 Sending Data
3xx - Provisional
  - 301 Ready to Receive
4xx - Client Failure
  - 401 Identity Unknown
5xx - Server Failure
6xx - <reserved>
7xx - <reserved>
8xx - <reserved>
9xx - <reserved>



Connection from Untrusted Client
------------------------------------------------------
  This interaction is the same, regardless of whether
  or not the server has proof of identity on file;

C: <connect>
S: hello, i am server.host.name                    S: HELO server.host.name
C: hello, my name is client.host.name              C: HELO client.host.name
S: I don't recognize you...                        S: 401 Identity Unknown

C: here is my proof of identity                    C: IDENT client.host.name 36b16e8d261850415b95b077c154fac50c2c93fb
S: ok, connect back in a bit                       S: 201 Identity Accepted for Review
   goodbye                                         S: BYE
   <disconnect>



Policy Retrieval for Trusted Client
------------------------------------------------------

C: <connect>
S: hello, i am server.host.name                    S: HELO server.host.name
C: hello, my name is client.host.name              C: HELO client.host.name
S: i remember you!                                 S: 202 Identity Confirmed

C: what's new with my policy?                      C: QUERY POLICY
S: latest version is 4.32.6                        S: 200 OK
                                                      VERSION 4.32.6

C: give me my policy                               C: RETRIEVE POLICY
S: policy found. stop when I say 'done'            S: 203 Sending Data
   POLICY DATA                                     S: <data>
   POLICY DATA                                     S: <data>
   POLICY DATA                                     S: <data>
   POLICY DATA                                     S: <data>
   done                                            S: DONE

C: thanks                                          C: BYE
   <disconnect>



Report Upload from Trusted Client
------------------------------------------------------

C: <connect>
S: hello, i am server.host.name                    S: HELO server.host.name
C: hello, my name is client.host.name              C: HELO client.host.name
S: i remember you!                                 S: 202 Identity Confirmed

C: here is my report                               C: STORE REPORT
S: go ahead                                        S: 301 Ready to Receive

C: stop when I say 'done'                          C: (no analog)
   REPORT DATA                                     C: <data>
   REPORT DATA                                     C: <data>
   REPORT DATA                                     C: <data>
   done                                            C: DONE
S: thanks                                          S: 200 OK
                                                      BYE
   <disconnect>




Example Policy Data Payload
------------------------------------------------------
policy Database Server
  version=x.y.z
res_user jrhunt
  passwd=$1$werjwoe
  uid=6001
  gid=2034
  gecos=James Hunt,,,
  pwmin=2
  pwmax=45
  pwwarn=7
res_user ndturner
  present=no
res_file /etc/sudoers
  mode=0400
DONE
